earing’.","History: The surname was brought to Scotland from southwestern England in the 12th century; Walter de Berchelai or Berkelai was Chamberlain of Scotland in 1165. It was long assumed that they were from the family that held Berkeley Castle in Gloucestershire, but the historian G. W. S. Barrow (1973, <i>The Kingdom of the Scots</i>) adduced evidence that they are more probably from Berkley in Somerset."]}]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah Barcley was born in 1457, in Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland. She married John Rankyn Burgess of Glasgow in 1500, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1457–":"1457–Surnud","1455–1487":"1455–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1457–Female":"1457–Surnud","1457":"1457","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1487":"1487","1480":"1480","Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1457–":"1457–Kuollut","1455–1487":"1455–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1457–Female":"1457–Kuollut","1457":"1457","1500":"1500","1455":"1